 .SH DESCRIPTION
@@
+ .SS NDB-configurable colors (optional)
+ .PP
+ Rio can optionally read its initial color scheme from NDB records. Rio searches, in this order,
+ .IR /usr/$user/lib/ndb/rio
+ and
+ .IR /lib/ndb/rio ,
+ for a record with attribute
+ .B service=rio
+ and an optional
+ .B theme
+ attribute.
+ When a matching record is found, the following keys are recognized (values are hex
+ .RI "#RRGGBB" ):
+ .B bg ,
+ .B fg ,
+ .B border ,
+ .B selbg ,
+ .B selfg ,
+ and
+ .B mouse .
+ If no matching record is present, rio falls back to its built-in defaults.
+ .PP
+ The effective colors are resolved with the following precedence:
+ built-in defaults,
+ then NDB,
+ then the
+ .B -b
+ option (black background),
+ and finally selections done at runtime via the
+ .B look
+ menu.
+ .PP
+ Example NDB entries:
+ .EX
+ service=rio theme=custom \\
+     bg=#101418 fg=#e6e6e6 border=#6c6c6c \\
+     selbg=#2e4a6f selfg=#ffffff mouse=#ffcc00
+ .EE
+
@@
 .SH FILES
@@
+.TP
+.I /lib/ndb/rio
+System-wide optional color definitions for rio (NDB).
+.TP
+.I /usr/$user/lib/ndb/rio
+Per-user optional color definitions for rio (NDB).
+
@@
 .SH ENVIRONMENT
@@
+.TP
+.B RIOTHEME
+If set, selects the value of the
+.B theme
+attribute to match in the NDB record (see
+.B NDB-configurable colors
+above).
+
